1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
MR. Robot Adversarial — SANS FIND EVIL! 2026
Autonomous AI cyber-defense pipeline.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
The problem: AI adversaries breach in under 8 minutes.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Our pipeline: scan → triage → adversarial review → verdict, in ~30 seconds.

4
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Three trust layers, two model families, one rule-based judge.

5
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Scanners are deterministic. The auditor is a different model family
than the triage agent — agreement actually carries information.

6
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Health check — providers, scanners, audit DB all online.

7
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Sample 1: a Python bind shell. Expected verdict: MALICIOUS.

8
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Step 1: deterministic scanners (skill, IOC, YARA, secrets) light up.
Step 2: MR. Robot (Nemotron) runs a 5-phase triage.

9
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Step 3: Falsifier (DeepSeek) audits the triage.
ΔA = 1.0 — propagator and auditor are different families.

10
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Verdict: MALICIOUS. Audit trail records every step.

11
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Sample 2: a Django view with parameterized ORM. Expected: BENIGN.

12
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:30,000
The Falsifier is framework-aware: it knows Django auto-escapes
and that .filter() parameterizes — no SQL injection vector.

13
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Verdict: BENIGN. Without the Falsifier this is a likely false alarm.

14
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Sample 3: an obfuscated npm worm. Triage uncertain on the first pass.

15
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Falsifier challenges the verdict → MR. Robot re-runs with the counter-argument.

16
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Max 2 iterations — beyond that, same-family re-runs amplify error
rather than reduce it (Shehata & Li 2026).

17
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Verdict on the worm: MALICIOUS after 2 iterations.

18
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Accuracy on 118 ground-truth samples (99 malicious + 19 benign):
Recall 100%, Precision 97.1%, F1 0.985, FPR 15.8%.

19
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Three false positives are listed in the report — we surface them,
we don't suppress them.

20
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Audit trail (SANS requirement #8): every tool call logged
to SQLite WAL with verdict, confidence, ΔA, and kinship-lock flag.

21
